olive oil
1 bag mint
1 packet walnuts
1 bag slaw mix
1 packet Mustard Cider Dressing
1 apple

Thinly slice the apple into half-moons. Pick and thinly slice the mint leaves.
Roughly chop the walnuts.

Heat a medium frying pan over a medium-high heat. Add the walnuts and
toast, tossing, until golden, 3-4 minutes.

In a large bowl, combine the apple, mint, slaw mix and mustard cider
dressing. Season with salt and pepper.

Transfer the apple and mint slaw to a serving bowl. Top with the
toasted walnuts.